{
  "macro_id": "retail.customerLTV",
  "domain": "retail",
  "name": "customerLTV",
  "inputs": {
    "avgOrderValue": { "type": "number", "required": false },
    "purchaseFrequencyPerYear": { "type": "number", "required": false },
    "customerLifespanYears": { "type": "number", "required": false },
    "cac": { "type": "number", "required": false },
    "customers": { "type": "array", "required": false }
  },
  "invariants": [
    "typeof output === 'object' && output !== null",
    "typeof output.ok === 'boolean'",
    "output.ok === false || output.result.ltv === undefined || Number.isFinite(output.result.ltv)",
    "output.ok === false || output.result.ltvToCacRatio === undefined || Number.isFinite(output.result.ltvToCacRatio)",
    "output.ok === false || output.result.cac === undefined || Number.isFinite(output.result.cac)",
    "output.ok === false || output.result.avgOrderValue === undefined || Number.isFinite(output.result.avgOrderValue)",
    "output.ok === true || typeof (output.error || output.message) === 'string'"
  ],
  "fuzz_cases": [
    { "input": { "avgOrderValue": 120, "purchaseFrequencyPerYear": 6, "customerLifespanYears": 2.5, "cac": 300 }, "expect": { "ok": true } },
    { "input": { "avgOrderValue": 50, "purchaseFrequencyPerYear": 2, "customerLifespanYears": 1, "cac": 80 }, "expect": { "ok": true } },
    { "input": { "avgOrderValue": 100, "purchaseFrequencyPerYear": 4, "customerLifespanYears": 3, "cac": 0 }, "expect": { "ok": true } },
    { "input": { "avgOrderValue": "1e999", "purchaseFrequencyPerYear": "Infinity", "customerLifespanYears": "NaN", "cac": -5 }, "expect": { "ok": true } },
    { "input": { "avgOrderValue": "abc", "purchaseFrequencyPerYear": "x", "customerLifespanYears": "y", "cac": "z" }, "expect": { "ok": true } },
    { "input": {}, "expect": { "ok": true } }
  ],
  "_note": "LENS_ACTIONS handler (server/domains/retail.js). 3-arg dispatch via /api/lens/run on key 'retail.customerLTV'. Drives the RetailActionPanel LTV card: flat unit-economics branch reads { avgOrderValue, purchaseFrequencyPerYear, customerLifespanYears, cac } and returns { avgOrderValue, purchaseFrequency, customerLifespanYears, ltv, cac, ltvToCacRatio, profitable }. ltv = AOV × freq/yr × lifespan(yr). FAIL-CLOSED: poisoned numerics → finite default (0); cac=0 collapses the ratio to ltv (never Infinity). Legacy customers[]-array branch (order-history LTV report) preserved for back-compat callers. Authored spec pinned by server/tests/retail-lens-macros.test.js."
}
